  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b87\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0bae\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0ba3\u0bc6\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0ba3\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Kerosene comes from India",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Douglas Devananda, Secretary General of the Eelam People's Democratic Party and Minister of Fisheries said that steps are being taken to bring 3 lakh containers of kerosene from India to Sri Lanka.",
        "In addition, the unavailability of kerosene is seen as a negative factor for farmers and fishermen in Sri Lanka to continue their economic activities.",
        "We are in talks with a private company in India to resolve the issue and we have reached a favorable decision to import 3 lakh containers with a capacity of 210 liters.",
        "I have discussed with Minister of Shipping Nimal Siripala de Silva the arrangements for the shipment and have also telephoned the Secretary of Defense for permission from the Ministry of Defense.",
        "Therefore, in the current crisis situation, kerosene will be imported from India as soon as possible to protect the livelihoods of farmers and fishermen, he added. (R)"
      ],
